  "doc_id": "11165",
  "text": "Like its orthologs in lower eukaryotes, the mammalian target of rapamycin (mTOR) is a multidomain protein and a member of the family of phosphoinositide (PI) 3-kinase-related kinases [PIKKs; which also include ATM and ATR, proteins involved in DNA repair (17) ]. Major features of mTOR are depicted in FIGURE 1A. Genetic knockouts of mTOR have revealed it to be an essential gene: mice lacking mTOR die in utero shortly after implantation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Embryonic development appears to be arrested at E5.5, with evidence of multiple developmental aberrations.",
